{"add":{"doc":{"id":"1b577c889ad6832724abbf6ad89b8330e7dd5c2608e5ffde581c39dcc9e4f787","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Volkswagen_Squareback_%28Type_III%29%2C_1973.jpg/220px-Volkswagen_Squareback_%28Type_III%29%2C_1973.jpg","previous":[],"after":["In 1964, Volkswagen acquired Auto Union, and in 1969, NSU Motorenwerke AG (NSU). The former company owned the historic Audi brand, which had disappeared after the Second World War. VW ultimately merged Auto Union and NSU to create the modern Audi company, and would go on to develop it as its luxury vehicle marque. The purchase of Auto Union and NSU proved to be a pivotal point in Volkswagen's history, as both companies yielded the technological expertise that proved necessary for VW to survive when demand for its air-cooled models went into decline."]}}}